348
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:39,680
That's true. Although I will say that some 
of the most time-wasting frameworks have  

349
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:44,760
also just come out of big companies, or 
the context of the big company that may  

350
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:50,840
have made that framework super useful within 
that context doesn't translate to startup  

351
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:56,440
or small company or even big company that 
doesn't have the rest of the context set,  

352
00:30:57,480 --> 00:31:05,400
but I don't think ... He's not wrong. I also just 
think big companies share the blame on that one.

353
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:09,080
I guess we should all just come back 
to PHP and jQuery and be simple.

354
00:31:09,080 --> 00:31:10,120
Maybe.

355
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:14,680
Okay, so to close out this 
thread on engineering leaders,  

356
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:19,880
finding the right balance, just to summarize 
your advice here. One is get to mastery before  

357
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:23,200
and is your advice here, get to this 
point before you move into engineering.

358
00:31:23,200 --> 00:31:30,840
Engineering management. I will say part of this is 
also in particular, if you happen to be a woman or  

359
00:31:30,840 --> 00:31:36,600
otherwise, underrepresented person in tech because 
people will tend to underestimate your technical  

360
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:42,400
abilities just unfortunately as a get-go. 
I also think it's particularly important to  

361
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:48,640
kind of develop that internal confidence in your 
abilities before you make this sort of scary leap,  

362
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:53,920
which is scary for everyone of have a ... if you 
have that mastery before you make the leap, I wish  

363
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:58,360
more people would do this because honestly, I do 
think there are a lot of people who never really  

364
00:31:58,360 --> 00:32:05,440
gained the mastery. They go into management, they 
lose it and some of them are still perfectly good  

365
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:09,480
managers and look, there are good managers 
who were never technical to begin with. 

366
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:14,080
I don't want to say that that's impossible. I 
just think that if you care about being technical,  

367
00:32:14,080 --> 00:32:21,160
if you are technical now and you want to maintain 
that tech-savvy, don't just become a manager the  

368
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:28,320
first time somebody offers it to you. Make sure 
you've really spent your good time writing code.

369
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:30,280
Is there a number of years 
heuristic you think about  

